# User dictionary auto-phrase rules.
# Base rules are declared here; compatible variants are generated by the engine.
# Single-char source selection rules:
# - Prefer the longest actual code; if a 4-code entry exists, do not fall back to short-code variants.
# - For 1-code chars, p12/p13/p22/p23 use 'v' as padding.
# - For 2-code chars, p13 uses p12 and p23 uses p22.
# Compatible phrase-code variants generated by the engine:
# - 2-char phrases: primary p11+p13+p21+p23, plus one compatible form p11+p12+p21+p22.
# - 3-char phrases: p11+p21+p23+p31 and p11+p21+p22+p31.
# - 4-char phrases: only p11+p21+p31+p41.
# - 5-12 char phrases: primary p11+p21+p31+p41, plus one compatible form p11+p21+p31+last-char-head.
# - If primary and compatible forms collapse to the same code, keep only one entry.
# yuninput:construct_phrase=^
# yuninput:rule:e2=p11+p12+p21+p22
# yuninput:rule:e3=p11+p21+p23+p31
# yuninput:rule:a4=p11+p21+p31+p41